HEADWORD: Short circuit
<hw>Short" cir"cuit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A circuit
formed or closed by a conductor of relatively low resistance because
shorter or of relatively great conductivity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

